from sklearn.preprocessing import OneHotEncoder

# One-hot encode categorical store_id
encoder = OneHotEncoder(sparse_output=False, drop='first')  
store_encoded = encoder.fit_transform(df[['store_id']])
store_encoded_df = pd.DataFrame(store_encoded, columns=encoder.get_feature_names_out(['store_id']))

# Reset index before concatenating to avoid index mismatch
store_encoded_df.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)
df.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)

# Concatenate the encoded store_id columns with the original dataframe
df = pd.concat([df, store_encoded_df], axis=1)

# Drop original categorical column
df.drop(columns=['store_id'], inplace=True)

In [202]:
# Define LSTM model
class LSTMModel(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, input_dim, hidden_dim, output_dim, num_layers):
        super(LSTMModel, self).__init__()
        self.hidden_dim = hidden_dim
        self.num_layers = num_layers
        self.lstm = nn.LSTM(input_dim, hidden_dim, num_layers, batch_first=True)
        self.fc = nn.Linear(hidden_dim, output_dim)

    def forward(self, x):
        h0 = torch.zeros(self.num_layers, x.size(0), self.hidden_dim)
        c0 = torch.zeros(self.num_layers, x.size(0), self.hidden_dim)
        out, _ = self.lstm(x, (h0, c0))
        out = self.fc(out[:, -1, :])
        return out

# Set hyperparameters
input_dim = X_train_tensor.shape[2]
hidden_dim = 24  # Reduced from 50
output_dim = 1
num_layers = 3  # Increased from 2
num_epochs = 200  # Increased from 100
learning_rate = 0.0005  # Reduced from 0.001
In [203]:
# Instantiate model for CPU
model = LSTMModel(input_dim, hidden_dim, output_dim, num_layers)
criterion = nn.MSELoss()
optimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=learning_rate)
In [204]:
# Train the model
model.train()
for epoch in range(num_epochs):
    for x_batch, y_batch in train_loader:
        outputs = model(x_batch)
        loss = criterion(outputs, y_batch)

        optimizer.zero_grad()
        loss.backward()
        optimizer.step()
    
    if (epoch + 1) % 10 == 0:
        print(f'Epoch [{epoch+1}/{num_epochs}], Loss: {loss.item():.4f}')
